b"Ok Wendy's im adding a little review of my own. Tonight i decided to try the new taco salad for dinner. I will say it's good but not liking the fact it's gotta be put together. A real taco salad is already made and mixed together before it's eaten. The price is ok but for 5.99 for a whole order that should come as a meal with fries and a drink. I had to buy my fries and drink separate.  But overall it's not to bad. Good job Wendy's."

b'I was at the Wendy\'s on Memorial Drive in Lancaster, OH between 6:30 and 6:45 pm on 12/8/16.  I ordered inside for a to go order.  The cashier was pleasant but didn\'t give me my receipt.  While waiting a man who has gray hair and was dressed as if he might be the manager was coordinating the orders at the counter.  When I approached he didn\'t greet me or say a word until he plunked my large chili and 10 chicken nuggets on the counter with "there\'s that."  I was waiting for a apple pecan chicken salad and once ready he shoved it into the bag sideways, dropped the dressing packets on the floor, picked them up and put them in the bag with the salad.  I asked if he had the pecans in the bag and he did not, I asked if the requested sweet and sour sauce was in the bag and it was not.  I gave him the dressing back--I didn\'t want it but told him that I really didn\'t want it since it had been on the floor.  He threw them back in the cooler.  While I was waiting to order a young man was standing between the drive thru area and front counter and for about 20 seconds he worked on styling his manbun before going to work without washing his hands.  I though the manager was going to say something to him as he was nearby but did not.  To top it off, once I got home I had about 1/3 cup of water in the bottom of my salad container--I had to strain it to eat it.  I was really looking forward to the salad but this whole experience was the worst I\'ve had for a very long time.  Please respond with your remedy--like improved manager attitude or hire somebody who cares for a start.  I realize this may be a franchise unit but your brand is on the line.  I have reached out to the company about this situation 3 times but nobody seems to be concerned other that the Facebook monitor who\'s response was, "Oh, no!, that is horrible!  I will have somebody contact you."  This just isn\'t bad service and food but a whole string of health code violations observed in just those few minutes.  If you don\'t want to do the job right, get out of the food service business.'
b'Think my Junior Bacon CheeseBURGER is missing something!'
b"At Wendy's on N Lee Street in Forsyth, Georgia"

b'Sat in line at Wendy\'s in Danville, Virginia, for at least 20 minutes.  When I placed my order of 1 medium chocolate frosty and a $25 gift card, was told to wait a minute 2 times and then the girl came back and we are out of gift cards.  Get to window to pick up my frosty and was asked "do you want a top on it?"  I said it doesn\'t matter.  She said well we don\'t have any tops.  I said y\'all don\'t have anything tonight do you?  The 3 standing at the window said no.  I overheard the people in the car ahead of me placing their order and were told they didn\'t have whatever they wanted.  Dave would be ashamed of the way his business has gone downhill.'

b"Ok, so I went to Wendy's in Marion Ark today for the first time and got an order of Chili. I have always loved it but haven't had any in a while. \nThe small was 1.89.  It was like eating a bowl of ketchup with beans .  Some of the beans were actually  crunchy from being undercooked. Now that I think about it I don't remember any meat! \n Not at all as good as it was a few years ago.  Might need to fix the or put it back on the value menu."

b'I don\'t normally make an issue over stuff like this.  However, we just had the worst customer service at Wendy\'s on South Washington in Holland, Michigan! We purchased four baked potatoes. My two older children and I ate our potatoes and thankfully my three year old refused hers. My eight year old was still hungry and started to eat into the remaining chive potato. However as she got about 1/3 of the potato eaten she found a bug right on the the edge of the inside and the skin. Upon further inspection, I found what appears to be a second "baked" bug on the outside of the skin as well. I called and explained the situation to the manager. They were less than helpful. After pressing, they said they would refund me the $1.59 for the single potato if I brought the potato back into the store as long as it was whole. Mind you, my daughter didn\'t see the bugs until she had eaten a portion of the potato. That in addition to the fact that I would have had to load my three kiddos back in the car and drive back to the store, wasn\'t worth the minimal refund or the hassle. I think we will just avoid Wendy\'s from here on out and give our money to places who offer better customer service.'

b"Is this how baconator fries should look? Bacon harder than glass shards and more burnt than a ginger in the summer with tanning oil on instead of sunblock. b"Went this evening to the WENDY'S at 409 E. Greenville st in Anderson, SC.  There was only two tables seated, no one in line and the carpet in the dining room was filthy. I'm thinking if you can see roach bugs in the light while the place is open, what's it like in there at night while it's closed? Place really needs a deep cleaning."

b'Very disappointed with my experience at the Wendy\'s Secaucus, NJ location! I ordered the sriracha chicken sandwich meal, and this is what I was served. No veggies, very little amount of bacon, no mayo spread. I thought the company motto is supposed to be "quality is our recipe"... clearly not at this location.'

b"I went to the Wendys in Homestead, PA off of 8th Avenue on 12-18-16 at approx 7:00 PM. I was the only customer inside the Wendy's there were approx 5-6 employees that were inside. I had to wait at least 5 minutes for the cashier to come and take my food order as she was in the back getting supplies, this was understandable, but once she took my order, the person that was to be making my burgers was on his phone, he was even told by someone in drive thru at one point, who I think may have been the manager but I am not sure, to take it in the back...this was his personal phone not the restaurant's phone, someone else was taking pictures with her phone & I was on my headset talking to a friend of mine who could here all the loud commotions and noises of the employees playing around and not working. The girl that took my order put my fries in a bag and left them under the light while the other guy that came from the back still talking on his phone started making my burgers, he messed them up and had to make them over as I watched him throw the buns away, both were without ketchup and one without tomatoes. He finally finished and put the burgers up to be bagged, which sat there another 2 minutes or so...by this time I was getting aggravated, and he asked are you waiting for these burgers to which I replied, I am not sure what I am waiting for, I am just trying to get my dinner. Someone else then said she is waiting on fries, I said no those are in the bags that have been sitting over there for 10 minutes, the cashier was now grabbing the fry bags and putting the burgers in them and the guy with the burgers said is there something wrong cuz your face looks like there is. I said I think it is a joke that you are on your phone, she taking pictures with hers and others are playing around while I am trying to get my food, he then said is there something wrong with your burgers, again I said I think this place is a joke to which someone else said and your ugly, I said excuse me? You are calling my ugly...give me my money back right now and I will be contacting Wendy's over this, he said no I was calling someone else in the back ugly....I said give me my money now....The same guy that had told him to go in the back with his phone was refunding me my money and then the burger guy came up and said I will be taking these and grabbed the bags off the counter, he said I will be throwing these away, and the manager or whoever he was that was, the drive thru guy that was refunding me my money said no don't throw that away we can use those fries. The cashier then counted out my money and took both receipts. I tried to get names but no one was wearing name tags that I could read. I had ordered a Single Combo and a Double with Cheese Combo both large and both with Frostys which I might add were not made either. I know that they will all get together and deny any of this, but if your cameras work there which they should, I want them pulled and you can see the way they were acting and carrying on and the person calling me ugly. I feel this is certainly discrimination against me. I am very upset and will never frequent that establishment or any Wendy's ever again and I will be letting everyone I know about this and putting it on Facebook as I am very mad. I do not usually let things bother me but this whole incident was uncalled for and you are paying people to play around instead of working"

b"After two years in East Asia, we finally got to spend time together in America! I came back to America four months before she did, so she made me swear I wouldn't have Wendy's fries and Frosties until we could have them together. So good to spend sweet time with a sweet friend!!"

b"Changing tables should seriously become a necessity. Do you know how gross it is to change your infants diaper on the floor in the bathroom?!? What would of happened if I changed him on your tables or booths,and let me tell you, it was a poopy diaper :)? I would've been judged, people would've made rude comments or glares, and been told it's not sanitary and disgusting. Well world, it's disgusting to change them in bathroom floors, especially when the bathrooms themselves look nasty. I'm so over having to do this at so many public places. Fix it. Seriously."

On the napkin wastw greasy fingerprints I called to complain after seeing that our burgers look raw and the manager laughed at me...I'm sick of not being able to trust anyone anymore you just don't know these days of some idiot is going to poison your food or do something gross but anyways no more wendys in Lebanon for me and I should get a refund."

b"Thanks for the number 8 Auburn, NY Wendy's. 
Asked for an asiago ranch chicken sandwich, and received a piece of chicken, some lettuce, and mayonnaise. 
Mayonnaise isn't an instrument Wendy. Neither is horseradish. But I'm sure glad I don't have some strange food allergies that prevent me from eating mayo. 
I get people have hard and long days. Believe me, it has been quite the day. But I waited 10 minutes, and spent $10 bucks, just to get home and find myself pretty disappointed.
I get it. Sometimes the two dressings look the same. Stuff happens. It can be tough to differentiate between ranch and mayonnaise at times.
But I would have been happier if they had at least put the cheese and tomatoes on, to make it look like they tried. 
Tell your staff to get some more sleep. Obviously they're lacking in the z's, with this holiday season upon us."

b"Good morning. I don't normally do things like this, but after my experience last night I think something needs to be said. I like Wendy\xe2\x80\x99s. The food normally always tastes fresh, and while it does typically take a few minutes longer than other fast food establishments to get my order, I understand that It is because the food cooked fresh, which I appreciate. Last night however was just terrible. I went to my local Wendy\xe2\x80\x99s at 1661 Hylan Blvd in Staten Island NY. It had been closed for a couple of months to undergo renovations and had opened back up this week. The new building and decor is beautiful, but that\xe2\x80\x99s where my good experience ended. I placed my order at 6:05pm. 2 fries, 2 sodas, a Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger, and a Dave\xe2\x80\x99s Single with no cheese for $15. I then waited over 25 minutes to actually get my meal. There were several people there waiting as well. At one point they stopped taking orders for 15 minutes to allow the kitchen to push out the orders. The staff had no idea what they were doing. None of them knew how to use the screen that displays the orders. There was no system in place and the training of the employees proved to be minimal. After finally getting my 2 burgers and fries 25 minutes after ordering, I sat down and opened the packaging to see two identical small burgers with cheese, and nothing else. No lettuce, no tomatoes, no onion or bacon. 2 sad little cheese burgers are a far cry from a Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger and a Single with no cheese. On top of all that, the food was horrible. It tasted terrible. I don\xe2\x80\x99t know what happened. We had a few bites and threw it out and left and went somewhere else for dinner. A big waste of 15 dollars. I hope this gets rectified soon, because everyone in that location yesterday was fed up, and if things don\xe2\x80\x99t change the business is going to suffer."

b'Just stopped at this Wendys

The tea... Took one sip. It was rancid. More like the urn hadn't been cleaned and the residue from lasr weeks tea made it into my cup.

Didnt drink the tea.

I scarfed down the beer bacon burger, which was flavorless for the most part and the onions just seemed different to me.

My wife didn't get halfway through hers. 

The onions were upsetting her stomach.

Now both of us feel ill. The kind of ill that makes you think its a stomach virus. The nauseous about to vomit kind.

Called the store. The "manager" was handed the phone. He didn't introduce himself. He did extend his gratitude for letting him know about the Tea. I'm down $29 now, thirsty, and the wife and I will likely be vomiting soon.

I will add that I've never seen a franchise use the corporate point of sale system to conduct business, while using separate merchant services equipment to process electronic forms of payment.

Kay

b'While I was ordering for us today at Wendy's in Coralville, IA, my daughter, who'd been climbing on the railing,  lost her balance and fell backward onto the floor and began crying immediately. When our food was ready, I noticed some ice cream on the tray. I was just about to correct the girl behind the counter when she said, "Hopefully this will make her elbow feel better!"

It was my daughter's fault that she fell and no one owed her anything. Yet, she'll be talking about this for a long time, so that dollar's worth of ice cream will mean more to her than millions spent on advertising.

As I was walking away,  I noticed the girl was employee of the month in March. With the compassionate display of customer service I saw, I'm not the least surprised!

Kudos to Wendy's and especially to Sarai Trigueros. If I had a vote, you'd be employee of the month for May, too!'

b"As I was sitting having lunch with my family at the Wendy's located at 3236 Ne Evangeline Trwy, Lafayette, LA, I noticed an older gentleman sit across from us with his meal.  Looking closer I saw that he was wearing a hat and jacket designating him as a veteran of the Korean war.  Having not been in line when he purchased his meal I decided to get a gift card as a thank you for his service. When I asked the manager behind the counter (sorry I didn't get her name) if I could put $8 on a gift card and explaining why she not only said yes, but added the $8 and zeroed it out and said it was on her!!! I presented the gentleman with the card and told him that on behalf of the team here at Wendy's and my family we would like to thank him for his service and buy his next meal at Wendy's. I feel so blessed that my son who is 6 got to see just how great people are and wish to thank your manager for being a part of it."
